# 🚀 Salesforce DX

Salesforce DX stands for Salesforce Developer Experience.

It is a modern development model designed for:
- Professional development
- Team collaboration
- Source-driven workflow
- Better deployment management

---

# 🔷 Features of Salesforce DX

## 1. Source-Driven Development
Source code becomes the primary source of truth.

### Benefits
- Easier tracking
- Better collaboration
- Safe deployment
- Simplified rollback

---

## 2. Scratch Orgs
Temporary Salesforce orgs used for:
- Testing
- Development
- Experimentation

---

## 3. GitHub Integration
DX supports:
- Git repositories
- Branch management
- Pull requests
- Team collaboration

---

## 4. Modern Workflow
Developers can work locally and deploy changes efficiently.

---

# 💻 Salesforce CLI

CLI stands for Command Line Interface.

Salesforce CLI allows developers to manage Salesforce projects using terminal commands.

---

# 🔷 Advantages of CLI

- Faster than browser workflow
- Supports automation
- Improves productivity
- Useful for deployments
- Better for enterprise projects

